1
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:12,791
[WHITE] I'm lucky enough to have
a family that I love very much.

2
00:00:12,875 --> 00:00:14,416
Benjamin Macbeth.

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,166
Emma Macbeth.

4
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:17,750
William Macbeth.

5
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:18,833
They all have it.

6
00:00:18,916 --> 00:00:20,333
[dinging]

7
00:00:20,416 --> 00:00:21,875
Mary Macbeth.

8
00:00:21,958 --> 00:00:22,791
[buzzer]

9
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:24,875
She does not have it.

10
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:28,541
The one and only blemish
in the Macbeth family tree?

11
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:29,416
[splatter]

12
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,375
Well, that would be me.

13
00:02:02,083 --> 00:02:04,750
[WHITE] It goes back
for generations.

14
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:08,083
Everyone in my family has been
born with psychic powers.

15
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:10,333
As a result, they've
all become casters,

16
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:12,541
a group of people
who use their powers

17
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:13,875
to help the world.

18
00:02:13,958 --> 00:02:16,250
So it's a long-standing
tradition on both sides

19
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,916
of our family
to become a caster.

20
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,500
Which means I should be
a first-class thoroughbred,

21
00:02:20,583 --> 00:02:23,291
and makes me even more
of a disappointment.

22
00:02:23,375 --> 00:02:24,833
[crying]

23
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:26,416
[WHITE]
Trust me on this one.

24
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:29,083
Being born an average kid into
a household of special people

25
00:02:29,166 --> 00:02:31,208
with special powers
is miserable.

26
00:02:31,291 --> 00:02:33,583
Nothing else to call it
but terrible luck.

27
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:35,500
[grunts]

28
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:37,875
[WHITE] I put myself on
trial on a daily basis.

29
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:38,958
[bleating]

30
00:02:39,041 --> 00:02:40,583
[YOUNG WHITE]
Miss Mary Macbeth!

31
00:02:40,666 --> 00:02:41,500
Guilty!

32
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:42,541
[WHITE]
However.

33
00:02:42,625 --> 00:02:44,333
[BEN]
Objection, your honor!

34
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:46,208
We find the
defendant innocent.

35
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,208
[bleating]

36
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,333
[WHITE]
I've got these parents.

37
00:02:48,416 --> 00:02:49,833
On what grounds, exactly?

38
00:02:49,916 --> 00:02:51,541
Do we have to spell it out?

39
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:54,625
You came into this world as
our one and only little girl.

40
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:56,875
Could there possibly be any
better grounds than that?

41
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:59,750
Not that I know of. That's
more than enough reason.

42
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:02,041
[EMMA] Oh, look at
those beautiful eyes.

43
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,708
They look just like emeralds.

44
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:05,458
[BEN]
Our priceless little treasure.

45
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:07,708
I wish. But they
really mean it.

46
00:03:07,791 --> 00:03:09,791
Trying to make me
feel good about myself

47
00:03:09,875 --> 00:03:11,250
only made me
feel even worse.

48
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,416
[EMMA]
You're so cute!

49
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,291
[WHITE] It's like
their unconditional love

50
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,583
just pointed out how
different I really was.

51
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,208
[EMMA]
You're so cute!

52
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:19,875
[WHITE]
Another reminder?

53
00:03:19,958 --> 00:03:21,791
[crying]

54
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,458
[WHITE]
My older brother.

55
00:03:23,541 --> 00:03:25,791
Not fair! He took it!
He took it from me!

56
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,666
[rumbling]

57
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:31,250
[dog barking]

58
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:34,708
Hey, Dad! Will's crying again!

59
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,125
[crying]

60
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,958
--[BULLY 1] C'mere, Wuss!
--[BULLY 2] Yeah, wussy!

61
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,666
[WHITE] My twin brother, born
just a few minutes ahead of me,

62
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:47,458
possessed enough power
for the both of us.

63
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:49,208
[BULLIES laughing]

64
00:03:49,291 --> 00:03:51,541
[WHITE] All of the casters
had high expectations

65
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:53,125
of him, as well.

66
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:54,333
And yet,

67
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:57,083
for reasons I don't understand,

68
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:59,500
he refused to ever
use his power.

69
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,791
[laughs weakly]

70
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:05,750
[YOUNG WHITE] Why don't you
ever try to fight back, Will?

71
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,541
There's just no reason
for you to always

72
00:04:07,625 --> 00:04:09,000
get your butt kicked, right?

73
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:10,291
[YOUNG BLACK]
I dunno.

74
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,708
[YOUNG WHITE]
Putting up with it is like

75
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:13,208
inviting them to
beat you up again.

76
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:16,125
[YOUNG BLACK]
Uh.

77
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,583
I know you're right, but
I'm not any good at fighting.

78
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:19,833
[frustrated grunt]

79
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:22,041
You don't have to use
your fists, you dummy!

80
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:23,541
Hmm?

81
00:04:23,625 --> 00:04:25,416
Psychic powers!

82
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,041
Uh.

83
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:29,958
You're sitting on a gold mine
and you won't even look down!

84
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:32,208
Ugh. Yeah, I'm sorry.

85
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:34,208
What are you apologizing for?

86
00:04:34,291 --> 00:04:35,083
Huh?

87
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:36,875
I don't want you to apologize!

88
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:38,208
Just use them!

89
00:04:38,291 --> 00:04:39,750
That's what I want, okay?

90
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,208
Oh, sorry.

91
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:44,541
[sighs]

92
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,375
[birds chirping]

93
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:47,916
Forget it.

94
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:51,500
Get beat up. It's your life.

95
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:55,166
[YOUNG BLACK]
Mary!

96
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:56,750
Hey, um.

97
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,708
Thank you.

98
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:59,375
Huh?

99
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:03,666
It's just that, I try not to,
but I always get scared.

100
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:06,708
I envy you, Mary.
I'm not strong like you are.

101
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:08,541
Don't be a smart aleck.

102
00:05:08,625 --> 00:05:09,708
Eh?

103
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:11,500
[WHITE] What does
he mean he gets scared?

104
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,833
The truth is that having
psychic powers isn't

105
00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:15,500
as great as it seems.

106
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:17,125
Using them causes fatigue.

107
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,291
And if you're reckless,

108
00:05:18,375 --> 00:05:20,291
it can even
shorten your life.

109
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,625
[grunting]

110
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:23,833
[splat]

111
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,250
[AUDIENCE gasps]

112
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,583
Scanning is exhausting.

113
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,041
Such a pain.

114
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,791
[WHITE] Maybe that's what
my brother's scared of.

115
00:05:32,875 --> 00:05:35,458
Taking years off of his life.

116
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,625
Or maybe not.

117
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,375
Maybe he's just a wimp.

118
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:41,416
No, your brother's not a wimp.

119
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,291
And don't you worry about him.

120
00:05:43,375 --> 00:05:45,375
Will's stronger than
he seems, he'll be fine.

121
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:47,875
I'm not worried. He can
be a wuss if he wants.

122
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,166
You and your mom can
be so ruthless some ti--

123
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,333
Uh, I meant strong-willed, so

124
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:55,791
he may come across
that way to you.

125
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,291
[bleating]

126
00:05:57,375 --> 00:06:00,708
[BEN] Choosing not to use
the easiest option available?

127
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:04,208
Well, that strikes me as
an incredibly brave decision.

128
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:06,291
And, it's all up to him.

129
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:09,625
There's no reason for him to
force himself to be a caster.

130
00:06:09,708 --> 00:06:12,500
Why should we make him do
something he doesn't want to?

131
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,166
[YOUNG WHITE grunting]

132
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,416
If he's thought it through
and that's what he's decided,

133
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,916
well, then, we have
to respect that.

134
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Not to mention.

135
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:22,125
Did you forget about
what happened?

136
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:24,750
The reason Will doesn't
want to use his powers now?

137
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,000
Hmm?

138
00:06:27,875 --> 00:06:29,083
I guess I did.

139
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:30,291
Really?

140
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:32,000
It was a pretty big
deal at the time.

141
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:34,458
Caused quite the commotion.

142
00:06:34,541 --> 00:06:36,500
Hey, Will.

143
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:37,708
C'mere, you gotta hear this.

144
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:40,041
Mary just told me
that she-- [grunts]

145
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:42,125
[YOUNG WHITE] Don't listen
to him, it's not important!

146
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,458
Hmm?

147
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,416
[YOUNG WHITE]
He can't be serious about

148
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,916
not being a caster.

149
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,250
[BOTH laughing]

150
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:52,375
[WHITE] My parents were
usually boring and normal.

151
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:54,208
[BOTH]
Bye.

152
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,250
[WHITE] So it made me really
proud whenever they'd go off

153
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:59,083
to save the world
from whatever danger.

154
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:00,500
But more than that,

155
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:02,666
I was downright
envious of them.

156
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,958
Getting to use their gifts
as weapons and risking

157
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,166
their lives for
the greater good.

158
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,291
Whether they've got
psychic powers or not,

159
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:11,458
everyone dies at some point.

160
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:14,375
Considering that, you have
to put some serious thought

161
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:17,833
into what you want to
accomplish before you croak.

162
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:20,000
Particularly if you're
nothing special.

163
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,791
There's gotta be something.

164
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:25,208
[camera clicks]

165
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:26,500
[YOUNG GIRLS]
Cheese!

166
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:33,875
[EMMA] Where in the world
did you find that old camera?

167
00:07:33,958 --> 00:07:35,666
[YOUNG WHITE]
In the closet.

168
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,750
Can I keep it?

169
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:37,875
Sure, why not?

170
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:39,916
It's your father's.

171
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,458
Do you like it?

172
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:44,125
Mm-hmm.

173
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:47,000
Well, I should get dinner
started before it gets too late.

174
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:50,625
[camera clicks]

175
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,541
[BEN]
You sure have taken a lot, huh?

176
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:55,041
[YOUNG WHITE]
Mm-hmm.

177
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,916
[BEN] Aren't there
any pictures of you?

178
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,083
[YOUNG WHITE]
Mm-mm.

179
00:07:58,166 --> 00:07:59,583
That's not what this is about.

180
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:02,708
[WHITE]
Honestly?

181
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:05,166
It's not like I had a passion
for photography or anything.

182
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:07,291
[footsteps approaching]

183
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:09,958
[BEN]
What is it about then?

184
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,166
[WHITE] It's just that if
I were to suddenly die

185
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,750
in the next instant.

186
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:16,333
At least the last thing I'd
seen would remain behind.

187
00:08:16,416 --> 00:08:17,416
[camera clicks]

188
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,958
And I thought that was nice.

189
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:21,041
That there'd still be
something left of me.

190
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,583
[gentle snoring]

191
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:24,041
But that's really all it was.

192
00:08:27,083 --> 00:08:29,000
[BULLY]
Hey, little wuss sister!

193
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:31,125
That's a pretty cool toy
you've got there.

194
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:32,708
[BULLY 2]
Yeah, we like it!

195
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,000
You wouldn't have a problem
with us borrowing it, right?

196
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:37,083
Yeah, hand it over!

197
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,333
Sure, why not.

198
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,208
[YOUNG BLACK]
Hold it!

199
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,083
[BULLIES laughing]

200
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:51,416
That camera belongs to
my sister, you jerks!

201
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,750
Now give it back!

202
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:54,041
Are you serious?

203
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:55,541
[BULLY 1] Calm down,
your sister's the one who

204
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:57,208
said we could use it.

205
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:59,458
Even so, I want it back!

206
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,416
She loves that camera!

207
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:04,833
Here.

208
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:08,208
[whooshing]

209
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:11,500
[camera rattles]

210
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:12,458
Got it!

211
00:09:12,541 --> 00:09:13,666
[screams]

212
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:20,791
[heartbeat]

213
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:22,625
[YOUNG BLACK]
Mary.

214
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:27,958
Why's your head on my chest?

215
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,000
I'm just making sure
you're still alive.

216
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:33,500
Oh, okay.

217
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:36,000
Where's Mom?

218
00:09:36,083 --> 00:09:37,333
She's on the phone.

219
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:43,375
[YOUNG WHITE] Why would you
jump into the river like that?

220
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:44,875
[YOUNG BLACK]
Those guys threw your camera

221
00:09:44,958 --> 00:09:47,000
and I was trying to catch it.

222
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,958
I guess I blew it
though, huh?

223
00:09:50,083 --> 00:09:51,875
I'm sorry.

224
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,625
I know how much you liked it.

225
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,958
[YOUNG WHITE] You know that you
could have died if those jerks

226
00:09:58,041 --> 00:10:00,375
hadn't pulled you
out of there, right?

227
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:01,625
Oh, yeah?

228
00:10:02,916 --> 00:10:04,958
I guess it was dangerous, huh?

229
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:06,875
I'll have to thank
them for that.

230
00:10:06,958 --> 00:10:09,125
[YOUNG WHITE]
What is wrong with you?

231
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:12,041
Why are you acting like this
happened to someone else?

232
00:10:12,125 --> 00:10:14,833
You're so stupid,
Will, I hate you!

233
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:17,041
You've always got that dumb
look on your face like

234
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:18,916
you don't know what's going on.

235
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,750
I don't care about the camera!

236
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,958
The pictures were just
a dumb distraction!

237
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,833
You must've been given your
power for a reason, right?

238
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:30,833
So use it.

239
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:32,958
Or whatever else you can.

240
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:35,708
Just do something
to protect yourself!

241
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:37,916
If you had died, Will.

242
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,250
If you had actually
drowned in the river.

243
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,916
Will,

244
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,833
if you had died.

245
00:10:47,916 --> 00:10:50,291
[YOUNG WHITE sobbing]

246
00:10:50,375 --> 00:10:52,875
I couldn't bear it!

247
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:57,583
[sobbing continues]

248
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:08,166
[BOTH crying]

249
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:17,250
Hey, what's the matter?

250
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,958
Why are you guys wailing?

251
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:24,791
[YOUNG BLACK]
I was just thinking.

252
00:11:24,875 --> 00:11:27,541
Do you remember when I broke
that mudball you made?

253
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:29,500
It was back when we
were really little.

254
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:34,333
It was such a well-made
and perfectly round ball.

255
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:35,666
And you seemed
so proud of it.

256
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:39,041
I think you showed it to me
hoping I would tell you

257
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:40,041
that you did a good job.

258
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,666
But it just made me frustrated.

259
00:11:44,875 --> 00:11:46,833
So I couldn't help
but make it explode.

260
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,708
Talk about childish.

261
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:53,291
Well, yeah. We were
