336
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Stay back!

337
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:26,250
It's not safe here!

338
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:30,500
[YOUNG WHITE]
And besides,

339
00:15:30,583 --> 00:15:32,125
Mom said
something one time.

340
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:34,333
She told me it
doesn't matter if a caster

341
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:36,541
is good at fighting
or if they're strong.

342
00:15:36,625 --> 00:15:38,291
That's not what
they actually need.

343
00:15:38,375 --> 00:15:39,791
[YOUNG BLACK]
Oh, yeah?

344
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:47,208
[BLACK] I'll let you have
my stupid body!

345
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:48,166
But please,

346
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:50,041
please, leave my sister alone!

347
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:54,041
I'm begging you!

348
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:58,833
But that's the only way!

349
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:00,958
If you need hands.

350
00:16:01,041 --> 00:16:02,375
If you have to take.

351
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,875
Then take what
you need from me!

352
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,125
[YOUNG WHITE] The one thing
that a caster really needs.

353
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:13,750
It's something that you've had
as long as I've known you, Will.

354
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,541
[WHITE]
I really am sorry, Leo.

355
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:22,500
[energy pulsing]

356
00:16:22,583 --> 00:16:23,833
[screams]

357
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,583
[pulsing continues]

358
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,041
I have to.

359
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:31,458
I don't want to do
this to you, but.

360
00:16:31,541 --> 00:16:33,000
I have to get Will back.

361
00:16:40,125 --> 00:16:42,291
And the only way
that I can do that.

362
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,750
Is for me to do what he wants.

363
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:48,250
[LEO winces]

364
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:49,583
[metallic clicking]

365
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,833
[WHITE]
Please forgive me.

366
00:17:00,916 --> 00:17:02,875
I can't go on
living in this world.

367
00:17:02,958 --> 00:17:03,958
[KING OF DESPAIR whistling]

368
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:06,791
[WHITE]
Not like this.

369
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:09,250
Not without my brother.

370
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:16,000
[whistling continues]

371
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,625
[KING OF DESPAIR]
You are absolutely correct

372
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:27,083
about one thing,
my dear sister.

373
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:29,625
Sooner or later,
everyone is bound to die.

374
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:32,041
Death!

375
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:34,250
Oh, death!

376
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:36,666
How ephemeral a thing.

377
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,875
So brief and defined.

378
00:17:38,958 --> 00:17:42,125
This terminal
predestination of man.

379
00:17:44,291 --> 00:17:47,666
However, I don't see
it as a tragedy.

380
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:50,500
Death is the ultimate
privilege of the living.

381
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:52,583
To exist beyond reason.

382
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:56,666
Roving lost and listless within
the confines of infinity.

383
00:17:56,750 --> 00:18:00,166
Yes, be grateful for
your fleeting nature.

384
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:04,125
It's impossible for one to live
and forget about death.

385
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:06,083
The despair that is my being.

386
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:09,125
Conversely forgotten
by death itself.

387
00:18:09,208 --> 00:18:11,250
There are few things
for me to embrace.

388
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:13,875
Only sleep,

389
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:18,416
and my yearning for twilight.

390
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:20,375
[KING OF DESPAIR]
Mornin'.

391
00:18:20,458 --> 00:18:23,000
You finally
wakin' up, brother?

392
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:26,208
Then it's about time
we got started...

393
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:29,416
with the finale!

394
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,708
[energy pulsing]

395
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,875
[crowd noise]

396
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:15,875
[quivering breath]

397
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:18,500
[WHITE]
Sonic?

398
00:19:18,583 --> 00:19:19,750
What're you doing here?

399
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,333
[WHITE laughs]

400
00:19:25,416 --> 00:19:26,791
Leo?

401
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:28,333
You're trying to find him?

402
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:35,875
[ticking]

403
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:44,666
[splat]

404
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,750
[SONIC whooping]

405
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,333
[WHITE whimpering]

406
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:00,666
[WHITE]
Hey. Sonic.

407
00:20:01,875 --> 00:20:03,375
Can you help me out?

408
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,958
Find Leo.

409
00:20:11,125 --> 00:20:14,208
[explosions]

410
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,208
[panting]

411
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:30,791
I think it's safe to say
this isn't your luckiest day,

412
00:20:30,875 --> 00:20:32,583
is it, old god eyes?

413
00:20:34,125 --> 00:20:35,958
[laughs]

414
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:39,625
As if I haven't already put you
through enough hell as it is.

415
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,250
Now you go and get yourself
possessed by a ghost.

416
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:45,333
[whistling]

417
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:48,458
[KING OF DESPAIR] I do hope you
realize that she's not human.

418
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:54,000
There's a barrier
in place of her heart.

419
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:56,541
It's the only thing
keeping her alive.

420
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:59,208
Nothing more than a
desperate last-ditch attempt

421
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:01,250
by her parents to keep
the feeble little brat

422
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:03,708
from croaking on them.

423
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:05,666
Lingering affection.

424
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:07,916
You. And me.

425
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,791
It's what's keeping us alive.

426
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:13,875
You're not the only one
who lost whatever remaining

427
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:16,500
hope you had that day.

428
00:21:16,583 --> 00:21:18,791
I went through
the same thing myself.

429
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:23,583
You do understand that
it has to be this way.

430
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:25,208
Don't you, Mary Macbeth?

431
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:29,875
If there's an efficacious
method that allows you to

432
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:31,750
achieve your objective.

433
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,583
Then you fully embrace it,

434
00:21:35,666 --> 00:21:37,458
no matter what it is.

435
00:21:37,541 --> 00:21:39,541
[gun rattles]

436
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:41,041
I bid you farewell,

437
00:21:41,125 --> 00:21:42,541
my sweet Mother Mary.

438
00:21:45,125 --> 00:21:46,625
I did love you.

439
00:21:46,708 --> 00:21:48,583
--[rumbling]
--[wind howling]

440
00:21:48,666 --> 00:21:49,833
[FEMT]
Well then.

441
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:52,708
Looks like the Second
Collapse finally begins.

442
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:55,958
Of course, leave it to him to
choose today of all days.

443
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:58,166
It's so obviously
freakin' droll that it loses

444
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:00,375
any trace of humor.

445
00:22:00,458 --> 00:22:02,375
Well, now what?

446
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:04,875
I mean, look how
dark it is in there.

447
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:07,875
