find our way home in that?

448
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:45,000
[KING OF DESPAIR] Greetings,
mirthful pumpkin-heads.

449
00:23:45,083 --> 00:23:46,791
Having fun out there tonight?

450
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:48,000
Playing any good tricks?

451
00:23:48,083 --> 00:23:49,500
Taking some treats?

452
00:23:49,583 --> 00:23:51,375
Call me the King of Despair.

453
00:23:51,458 --> 00:23:54,083
I've worked really hard to
prepare an extra special show,

454
00:23:54,166 --> 00:23:55,541
just for today.

455
00:23:55,625 --> 00:23:57,583
I do sincerely
hope you enjoy it,

456
00:23:57,666 --> 00:24:00,041
especially since you're
all performing in it.

457
00:24:00,125 --> 00:24:03,958
The name of this performance
will be, let's see here.

458
00:24:04,041 --> 00:24:06,166
How about "Sympathy
for the Devil."

459
00:24:07,583 --> 00:24:09,375
[LEO]
I have a younger sister.

460
00:24:09,458 --> 00:24:10,708
Not too long ago,

461
00:24:10,791 --> 00:24:13,125
this brave, noble,
charming sister of mine

462
00:24:13,208 --> 00:24:15,125
offered herself up
in place of me

463
00:24:15,208 --> 00:24:16,291
and lost her eyesight.

464
00:24:17,708 --> 00:24:19,291
This world around me.

465
00:24:19,375 --> 00:24:21,583
The world that I
see with her eyes.

466
00:24:21,666 --> 00:24:24,708
It's stunningly
beautiful, and cruel.

467
00:24:24,791 --> 00:24:28,291
And now that my eyes
are closed, it shines.

468
00:24:28,375 --> 00:24:30,958
Next time on
"Blood Blockade Battlefront,"

469
00:24:31,041 --> 00:24:32,625
Hello, world!

470
00:24:32,708 --> 00:24:34,000
Michella,

471
00:24:34,083 --> 00:24:35,166
more than ever,

472
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,833
I have to
tell you something.

